Class Node

  • java.lang.Object
    • Node

  • public class Node
extends java.lang.Object
    The Node object is the basic component of the Trie data structure. It contains several getter/setter methods that are needed for the operation of the Trie structure to implement the basic dictionary methods and for the computation of LCS and Edit Distance.

      • Node

        public Node(int id,
    char name)
        Creates a Node object that is used for the Trie data structure. The constructor is called only by the TrieReader when building according to the output of the TrieBuilder class.
        Parameters:
        id - The ID of a Node object is given by the TrieBuilder.
        name - The name of a Node object is the character value that is assigned to it.

        Checks whether the the current Node makes a complete word. Can also mean that the Node has a child that contains a '$' or end of word character.
        Returns:

        public void setVis(long val)

      • setDepth

        public void setDepth(int val)

        Parameters:

      • getDepth
